Package: ggseqlogoMOD
Type: Package
Title: An extension of ggseqlogo to draw publication-ready sequence logos
Version: 0.1
Date: 2017-07-25
Authors@R: c(
  person("Omar", "Wagih", , "omarwagih@gmail.com", role = c("aut")),
  person("Marthe", "Solleder", role = c("aut")),
  person("David", "Gfeller", , "david.gfeller@unil.ch", role = c("ctb"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-3952-0930")),
  person("Julien", "Racle", , "julien.racle@unil.ch", role = c("ctb", "cre"),
         comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-0100-0323")))
Description: This is a fork from ggseqlogo, allowing to draw highly versatile
    sequence logos. Features include, but not limited to, modifying colour schemes
    and fonts used to draw the logo, generating multiple logo plots, aiding the
    visualisation with annotations, and display non-canonical amino acids in
    different colors. Sequence logos can easily be combined with other 'ggplot2' plots.
License: LGPL
URL: https://github.com/GfellerLab/ggseqlogo
BugReports: https://github.com/GfellerLab/ggseqlogo/issues
